<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <title>SaaS Subscription Agreement</title>
    <style>
        body { font-family: 'Times New Roman', serif; line-height: 1.6; margin: 40px; }
        .header { text-align: center; margin-bottom: 30px; }
        .section { margin: 25px 0; }
        .clause { margin: 15px 0; }
        .fill-in { border-bottom: 1px solid #000; min-width: 150px; }
        h1 { font-size: 18px; text-align: center; text-transform: uppercase; }
        h2 { font-size: 16px; margin-top: 30px; color: #333; }
        h3 { font-size: 14px; margin-top: 20px; }
        table { width: 100%; border-collapse: collapse; margin: 15px 0; }
        th, td { border: 1px solid #000; padding: 8px; text-align: left; }
        th { background-color: #f0f0f0; }
        .pricing-box { border: 2px solid #000; padding: 15px; margin: 15px 0; background-color: #f9f9f9; }
        .sla-box { background-color: #e6f3ff; padding: 15px; border: 1px solid #0066cc; margin: 15px 0; }
        .important { background-color: #ffffcc; padding: 10px; border-left: 4px solid #ff0000; margin: 15px 0; }
        .checkbox { display: inline-block; width: 15px; height: 15px; border: 1px solid #000; margin-right: 5px; }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <div class="header">
        <h1>SOFTWARE AS A SERVICE (SAAS) AGREEMENT</h1>
        <h2>Subscription and Licensing Terms</h2>
        <p><strong>Service Provider:</strong> <span class="fill-in">_________________________</span></p>
        <p><strong>Customer:</strong> <span class="fill-in">_________________________</span></p>
        <p><strong>Effective Date:</strong> <span class="fill-in">_________________</span></p>
    </div>

    <div class="section">
        <h2>1. DEFINITIONS</h2>
        <p><strong>"Agreement"</strong> means this SaaS Agreement and any amendments.</p>
        <p><strong>"Customer"</strong> means the entity subscribing to the Service.</p>
        <p><strong>"Customer Data"</strong> means data, content, and information provided by Customer.</p>
        <p><strong>"Service"</strong> means the SaaS platform and related services provided by Provider.</p>
        <p><strong>"Users"</strong> means Customer's authorized employees and agents.</p>
        <p><strong>"Documentation"</strong> means user guides and technical specifications.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="section">
        <h2>2. SERVICE DESCRIPTION</h2>
        
        <div class="clause">
            <h3>2.1 SaaS Platform</h3>
            <p>Provider will provide Customer with access to the following SaaS platform:</p>
            <p><strong>Platform Name:</strong> <span class="fill-in">_________________________</span></p>
            <p><strong>Platform URL:</strong> <span class="fill-in">_________________________</span></p>
            
            <p><strong>Core Features Include:</strong></p>
            <p><span class="checkbox">☐</span> User management and authentication</p>
            <p><span class="checkbox">☐</span> Data storage and management</p>
            <p><span class="checkbox">☐</span> Analytics and reporting</p>
            <p><span class="checkbox">☐</span> API access and integrations</p>
            <p><span class="checkbox">☐</span> Mobile application access</p>
            <p><span class="checkbox">☐</span> Customer support</p>
            <p><span class="checkbox">☐</span> Other: <span class="fill-in">_________________________</span></p>
        </div>

        <div class="clause">
            <h3>2.2 Service Levels and Availability</h3>
            <div class="sla-box">
                <p><strong>SERVICE LEVEL AGREEMENT (SLA):</strong></p>
                <table>
                    <tr>
                        <th>Metric</th>
                        <th>Target</th>
                        <th>Measurement</th>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td>System Uptime</td>
                        <td><span class="fill-in">___</span>% monthly</td>
                        <td>24/7 monitoring</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td>Response Time</td>
                        <td>< <span class="fill-in">___</span> seconds</td>
                        <td>Page load times</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td>Data Recovery Time</td>
                        <td>< <span class="fill-in">___</span> hours</td>
                        <td>In case of outages</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td>Support Response</td>
                        <td>< <span class="fill-in">___</span> hours</td>
                        <td>Business hours</td>
                    </tr>
                </table>
                
                <p><strong>SLA Credits:</strong></p>
                <p>• <99% uptime: <span class="fill-in">___</span>% monthly fee credit</p>
                <p>• <95% uptime: <span class="fill-in">___</span>% monthly fee credit</p>
                <p>• <90% uptime: <span class="fill-in">___</span>% monthly fee credit</p>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="clause">
            <h3>2.3 Excluded Services</h3>
            <p>The following are excluded from this Agreement:</p>
            <p>• Custom development and integrations</p>
            <p>• Data migration from third-party systems</p>
            <p>• On-site training and consulting</p>
            <p>• Third-party software licenses</p>
            <p>• Hardware or infrastructure provision</p>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="section">
        <h2>3. SUBSCRIPTION TERMS</h2>
        
        <div class="pricing-box">
            <h3>3.1 Subscription Plans and Pricing</h3>
            <table>
                <tr>
                    <th>Plan</th>
                    <th>Users</th>
                    <th>Features</th>
                    <th>Monthly Price</th>
                    <th>Annual Price</th>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td>Starter</td>
                    <td>Up to <span class="fill-in">___</span></td>
                    <td>Basic features</td>
                    <td>₹<span class="fill-in">_____</span>/month</td>
                    <td>₹<span class="fill-in">_____</span>/year</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td>Professional</td>
                    <td>Up to <span class="fill-in">___</span></td>
                    <td>Advanced features</td>
                    <td>₹<span class="fill-in">_____</span>/month</td>
                    <td>₹<span class="fill-in">_____</span>/year</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td>Enterprise</td>
                    <td>Unlimited</td>
                    <td>All features</td>
                    <td>₹<span class="fill-in">_____</span>/month</td>
                    <td>₹<span class="fill-in">_____</span>/year</td>
                </tr>
            </table>
            
            <p><strong>Selected Plan:</strong> <span class="fill-in">_________________________</span></p>
            <p><strong>Billing Cycle:</strong> <span class="checkbox">☐</span> Monthly <span class="checkbox">☐</span> Annual</p>
            <p><strong>Number of Users:</strong> <span class="fill-in">_____</span> users</p>
            <p><strong>Monthly/Annual Fee:</strong> ₹<span class="fill-in">_________</span></p>
        </div>

        <div class="clause">
            <h3>3.2 Subscription Period</h3>
            <p><strong>Initial Term:</strong> <span class="fill-in">_____</span> months/years from Effective Date</p>
            <p><strong>Renewal:</strong> Automatic renewal for successive <span class="fill-in">_____</span> month/year periods</p>
            <p><strong>Termination Notice:</strong> <span class="fill-in">_____</span> days written notice required to avoid renewal</p>
        </div>

        <div class="clause">
            <h3>3.3 Usage Limits and Overages</h3>
            <p><strong>Included Limits:</strong></p>
            <p>• Storage: <span class="fill-in">_____</span> GB</p>
            <p>• Monthly Transactions: <span class="fill-in">_____</span></p>
            <p>• API Calls: <span class="fill-in">_____</span> per month</p>
            <p>• Bandwidth: <span class="fill-in">_____</span> GB transfer</p>
            
            <p><strong>Overage Charges:</strong></p>
            <p>• Additional Storage: ₹<span class="fill-in">_____</span> per GB</p>
            <p>• Extra Transactions: ₹<span class="fill-in">_____</span> per 1,000</p>
            <p>• Additional API Calls: ₹<span class="fill-in">_____</span> per 10,000</p>
            <p>• Extra Bandwidth: ₹<span class="fill-in">_____</span> per GB</p>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="section">
        <h2>4. PAYMENT TERMS</h2>
        
        <div class="clause">
            <h3>4.1 Payment Schedule</h3>
            <p><strong>Advance Payment:</strong> All fees payable in advance</p>
            <p><strong>Billing Date:</strong> <span class="fill-in">_____</span> of each month/year</p>
            <p><strong>Payment Due:</strong> Within <span class="fill-in">_____</span> days of invoice</p>
            <p><strong>Payment Methods:</strong></p>
            <p><span class="checkbox">☐</span> Credit/Debit Card (auto-renewal)</p>
            <p><span class="checkbox">☐</span> Bank Transfer/NEFT</p>
            <p><span class="checkbox">☐</span> Digital Wallet</p>
            <p><span class="checkbox">☐</span> Check/Demand Draft</p>
        </div>

        <div class="clause">
            <h3>4.2 Late Payment and Suspension</h3>
            <p><strong>Late Payment Penalty:</strong> <span class="fill-in">_____</span>% per month on overdue amounts</p>
            <p><strong>Suspension Notice:</strong> <span class="fill-in">_____</span> days written notice before suspension</p>
            <p><strong>Service Suspension:</strong> Non-payment may result in service suspension</p>
            <p><strong>Data Retention:</strong> Customer data retained for <span class="fill-in">_____</span> days during suspension</p>
        </div>

        <div class="clause">
            <h3>4.3 Refunds and Cancellation</h3>
            <p><strong>Refund Policy:</strong></p>
            <p><span class="checkbox">☐</span> No refunds on subscription fees</p>
            <p><span class="checkbox">☐</span> Pro-rata refunds for annual subscriptions</p>
            <p><span class="checkbox">☐</span> 30-day money-back guarantee</p>
            
            <p><strong>Cancellation:</strong></p>
            <p>• Customer may cancel with <span class="fill-in">_____</span> days notice</p>
            <p>• Service continues until end of paid period</p>
            <p>• No refund for partial months/years</p>
        </div>

        <div class="clause">
            <h3>4.4 Taxes and Fees</h3>
            <p><strong>Tax Responsibility:</strong> Customer responsible for applicable taxes</p>
            <p><strong>GST:</strong> GST will be charged as per Indian tax law</p>
            <p><strong>TDS:</strong> Customer responsible for TDS deduction and certificate</p>
            <p><strong>Transaction Fees:</strong> Payment processing fees may apply</p>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="section">
        <h2>5. DATA AND SECURITY</h2>
        
        <div class="clause">
            <h3>5.1 Customer Data</h3>
            <div class="important">
                <p><strong>DATA OWNERSHIP:</strong> Customer retains all rights to Customer Data</p>
            </div>
            <p><strong>Data Use License:</strong> Customer grants Provider limited license to process data solely for service provision</p>
            <p><strong>Data Export:</strong> Customer may export data in standard formats</p>
            <p><strong>Data Deletion:</strong> Customer data deleted within <span class="fill-in">_____</span> days after termination</p>
        </div>

        <div class="clause">
            <h3>5.2 Security Measures</h3>
            <p><strong>Data Encryption:</strong></p>
            <p>• Data in transit: TLS 1.2+ encryption</p>
            <p>• Data at rest: AES-256 encryption</p>
            <p>• Database encryption with key management</p>
            
            <p><strong>Access Controls:</strong></p>
            <p>• Multi-factor authentication required</p>
            <p>• Role-based access permissions</p>
            <p>• Regular access reviews and audits</p>
            <p>• Session management and timeouts</p>
            
            <p><strong>Infrastructure Security:</strong></p>
            <p>• SOC 2 Type II certified data centers</p>
            <p>• Firewall and intrusion detection</p>
            <p>• Regular security updates and patches</p>
            <p>• 24/7 security monitoring</p>
        </div>

        <div class="clause">
            <h3>5.3 Data Backup and Recovery</h3>
            <p><strong>Backup Schedule:</strong></p>
            <p>• Daily automated backups</p>
            <p>• <span class="fill-in">_____</span> days backup retention</p>
            <p>• Geographic backup redundancy</p>
            
            <p><strong>Recovery Procedures:</strong></p>
            <p>• Recovery Time Objective (RTO): <span class="fill-in">_____</span> hours</p>
            <p>• Recovery Point Objective (RPO): <span class="fill-in">_____</span> hours</p>
            <p>• Customer notification of recovery events</p>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="section">
        <h2>6. USER MANAGEMENT AND ACCEPTABLE USE</h2>
        
        <div class="clause">
            <h3>6.1 User Accounts</h3>
            <p><strong>Administrator Rights:</strong> Customer designates system administrators</p>
            <p><strong>User Provisioning:</strong> Customer responsible for adding/removing users</p>
            <p><strong>Password Policy:</strong> Strong password requirements enforced</p>
            <p><strong>Account Security:</strong> Customer responsible for account security</p>
        </div>

        <div class="clause">
            <h3>6.2 Acceptable Use Policy</h3>
            <p><strong>Permitted Uses:</strong></p>
            <p>• Business purposes consistent with service features</p>
            <p>• Compliance with all applicable laws</p>
            <p>• Authorized user access only</p>
            
            <p><strong>Prohibited Uses:</strong></p>
            <p>• Illegal or fraudulent activities</p>
            <p>• Violating third-party rights</p>
            <p>• Reverse engineering or hacking attempts</p>
            <p>• Excessive resource consumption</p>
            <p>• Spam or unsolicited communications</p>
            <p>• Virus or malware distribution</p>
        </div>

        <div class="clause">
            <h3>6.3 Suspension Rights</h3>
            <p>Provider may suspend service for:</p>
            <p>• Violation of acceptable use policy</p>
            <p>• Non-payment of fees</p>
            <p>• Security threats or breaches</p>
            <p>• Legal or regulatory requirements</p>
            
            <p><strong>Suspension Notice:</strong> <span class="fill-in">_____</span> hours notice (except emergencies)</p>
            <p><strong>Reinstatement:</strong> Service restored upon issue resolution</p>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="section">
        <h2>7. SUPPORT AND MAINTENANCE</h2>
        
        <div class="clause">
            <h3>7.1 Support Services</h3>
            <table>
                <tr>
                    <th>Support Level</th>
                    <th>Availability</th>
                    <th>Response Time</th>
                    <th>Channels</th>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td>Standard</td>
                    <td>Business Hours</td>
                    <td><span class="fill-in">___</span> hours</td>
                    <td>Email, Chat</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td>Priority</td>
                    <td>Extended Hours</td>
                    <td><span class="fill-in">___</span> hours</td>
                    <td>Email, Chat, Phone</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td>Premium</td>
                    <td>24/7</td>
                    <td><span class="fill-in">___</span> minutes</td>
                    <td>All channels + dedicated</td>
                </tr>
            </table>
            
            <p><strong>Support Level:</strong> <span class="fill-in">_________________________</span></p>
        </div>

        <div class="clause">
            <h3>7.2 Maintenance and Updates</h3>
            <p><strong>Scheduled Maintenance:</strong></p>
            <p>• Planned maintenance windows: <span class="fill-in">_____</span> hours/month</p>
            <p>• Advance notice: <span class="fill-in">_____</span> hours minimum</p>
            <p>• Preferred maintenance time: <span class="fill-in">_____</span></p>
            
            <p><strong>Software Updates:</strong></p>
            <p>• Automatic security updates</p>
            <p>• Feature updates with notification</p>
            <p>• Customer testing environment available</p>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="section">
        <h2>8. WARRANTIES AND LIABILITY</h2>
        
        <div class="clause">
            <h3>8.1 Service Warranties</h3>
            <p>Provider warrants that:</p>
            <p>• Service will substantially conform to Documentation</p>
            <p>• Service will be performed in workmanlike manner</p>
            <p>• Provider has rights to provide the Service</p>
            <p>• Service will not infringe third-party rights</p>
            
            <p><strong>Remedy:</strong> Re-performance of non-conforming services</p>
            <p><strong>Warranty Period:</strong> Duration of subscription</p>
        </div>

        <div class="clause">
            <h3>8.2 Disclaimer</h3>
            <div class="important">
                <p><strong>EXCEPT AS EXPRESSLY STATED, SERVICE PROVIDED "AS IS" WITHOUT WARRANTIES OF ANY KIND</strong></p>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="clause">
            <h3>8.3 Limitation of Liability</h3>
            <p><strong>Liability Cap:</strong> Each party's total liability limited to fees paid in 12 months preceding claim</p>
            <p><strong>Excluded Damages:</strong> No liability for indirect, consequential, or special damages</p>
            <p><strong>Exceptions:</strong> No limitation for confidentiality breaches, IP infringement, or willful misconduct</p>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="section">
        <h2>9. TERMINATION</h2>
        
        <div class="clause">
            <h3>9.1 Termination Rights</h3>
            <p><strong>By Customer:</strong> <span class="fill-in">_____</span> days notice for convenience</p>
            <p><strong>By Provider:</strong> <span class="fill-in">_____</span> days notice for convenience</p>
            <p><strong>For Cause:</strong> Immediate termination for material breach (30-day cure period)</p>
        </div>

        <div class="clause">
            <h3>9.2 Effect of Termination</h3>
            <p><strong>Service Access:</strong> Terminates at end of paid period</p>
            <p><strong>Data Export:</strong> <span class="fill-in">_____</span> days to export Customer Data</p>
            <p><strong>Data Deletion:</strong> Customer Data deleted after export period</p>
            <p><strong>Refunds:</strong> As per refund policy above</p>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="section">
        <h2>10. GENERAL PROVISIONS</h2>
        
        <div class="clause">
            <h3>10.1 Governing Law</h3>
            <p><strong>Governing Law:</strong> Laws of India</p>
            <p><strong>Jurisdiction:</strong> Courts of <span class="fill-in">[City]</span>, India</p>
            <p><strong>Dispute Resolution:</strong> Arbitration under Indian Arbitration Act</p>
        </div>

        <div class="clause">
            <h3>10.2 Changes to Agreement</h3>
            <p><strong>Material Changes:</strong> <span class="fill-in">_____</span> days advance notice</p>
            <p><strong>Fee Changes:</strong> <span class="fill-in">_____</span> days notice, effective next renewal</p>
            <p><strong>Customer Options:</strong> Accept changes or terminate subscription</p>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div style="margin-top: 40px; border-top: 2px solid #000; padding-top: 20px;">
        <h2>EXECUTION</h2>
        <p>By clicking "I Agree" or using the Service, Customer agrees to be bound by this Agreement.</p>
        
